This paper discusses the use of statistical machine learning approaches for natural language generation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also addresses the need for reliable evaluation metrics and high-quality corpora, which are common issues in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software engineering (cs.SD).
